{"builtWith":"0.15.15","comments":[{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":"                                     // hydrogen // schema // audio // formant"},{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":" | Formant and vocal tract modeling atoms for speech synthesis."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Formant Theory"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Formants are resonant frequencies of the vocal tract. The first two"},{"LineComment":" | formants (F1, F2) are sufficient to distinguish most vowels. F1 relates"},{"LineComment":" | to tongue height (open/closed), F2 to front/back position."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Vowel Space"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | The F1×F2 plane defines the vowel space. Every vowel sound corresponds"},{"LineComment":" | to a point in this plane, enabling deterministic vowel synthesis."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Vocal Tract Model"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | The vocal tract acts as a series of resonant filters. Formant frequencies"},{"LineComment":" | and bandwidths define the filter characteristics. This enables both"},{"LineComment":" | speech synthesis and voice transformation (vocoding)."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Usage"},{"LineComment":" | ```purescript"},{"LineComment":" | import Hydrogen.Schema.Audio.Formant as Formant"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | -- Define the vowel /a/ (as in \"father\")"},{"LineComment":" | vowelA = Formant.vowel"},{"LineComment":" |   (Formant.f1 800.0)   -- Low F1 = open"},{"LineComment":" |   (Formant.f2 1200.0)  -- Mid F2 = central"},{"LineComment":" |   (Formant.f3 2500.0)"},{"LineComment":" | ```"}],"decls":[],"exports":[],"foreign":[],"imports":[{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[118,14],"start":[107,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","Schema","Audio","Forman